==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Haematic
<hw>Hae*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(h⟦esl⟧*m⟦acr⟧t"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>a"imatiko`s</grk>]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the
blood; sanguine; brownish red.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Haematic acid</b></col> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>, <cd>a
hypothetical acid, supposed to be formed from hemoglobin during its
oxidation in the lungs, and to have the power of freeing carbonic acid
from the sodium carbonate of the serum.</cd>
<rj><au>Thudichum.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Haematin</ent>⟦br⟧
